	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have two of RetroUSB's devices -- the SNES-to-USB adapter, and the NES-to-USB adapter.  If you have questions about how they work, let me know.
<br />
<br />And yeah, they strictly adhere to the USB HID class -- no drivers needed.  The USB device name they show up under in Windows is "SNES" and "NES" as well, which is an added bonus.  (Some people DO adhere to the standard... thank god.  :) )

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


